You could imagine giving either answer. In the olden days of traditional ba=
nking, it might have made sense for a central bank to lend against banks=E2=
=80=99 loans at their face value. But modern central bankers are plugged in=
to financial markets, and financial markets are good at determining market =
prices for assets, and so the modern consensus seems to be that central ban=
ks should lend against collateral at its market value.
