   =20
      Programming note
   =20
 =20

Money Stuff was supposed to be off on Friday, but then Silicon Valley Bank =
collapsed and   there was an unscheduled Money Stuff. Back when Elon Musk w=
as trying to buy or not buy=C2=A0Twitter, that sort of thing happened a lot=
, to the point that  the Verge published a story titled =E2=80=9CA brief hi=
story of Elon Musk sabotaging Matt Levine=E2=80=99s=C2=A0time off.=E2=80=9D=
=C2=A0This is enough of a thing that people sometimes=C2=A0joke on Twitter =
about buying index options whenever I write =E2=80=9CMoney Stuff will be of=
f tomorrow,=E2=80=9D on the theory that the market gods always get up to so=
mething crazy whenever I try to take a day off.
Naturally someone did a backtest and turns out it=E2=80=99s a bad idea (not=
 investing advice!). Here is =E2=80=9CA Matt Levine Effect?=E2=80=9D by Pau=
l Connell, William Fallon and Nicholas Foretek, on SSRN and everything:
This paper constructs a novel dataset to explore whether Matt Levine=E2=80=
=99s vacation drives market volatility as suggested by readers and Levine h=
imself. It finds that contrary to expectations, Levine=E2=80=99s vacations =
have an (almost) statistically significant effect in the opposite direction=
: decreasing market volatility. This paper provides a series of potential e=
xplanations for this observed market reaction.
The main explanation is that I take vacations at normal vacation times, whe=
n everyone else takes vacations and markets are often quiet. The paper is f=
ull of good sentences, including =E2=80=9CThe measured effect of Matt Levin=
e=E2=80=99s vacations on financial market volatility is negative and of a c=
onsiderable magnitude,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CThis paper contributes to two bodi=
es of research. The first is a collection of studies that examine spurious =
statistical correlates of important macroeconomic events,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=9CTo our knowledge, we are the first to combine Money Stuff publication da=
tes, VIX closing data, federal bank holidays and sunspot records into a sin=
gle database=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CCollection of the data for this study wa=
s made possible by the authors=E2=80=99 status as graduate students who, if=
 our advisors are asking, definitely spent the whole week before spring bre=
ak working on our dissertations.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0

