00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
deposit beta</a>=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0the sensitivity of bank deposit ra=
te increases=C2=A0to Fed interest rate increases =E2=80=94=C2=A0is lower th=
an 1. So if the Fed raises rates from 0% to 3%, you might end up paying onl=
y, say, 0.5% on deposits.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" s=
