<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So you go to your lender of last resort, let=
=E2=80=99s say the Federal Reserve. You say: =E2=80=9CHere is a $100 asset =
that I have. I want to post it as collateral for a loan. You lend me $100 a=
gainst this collateral, and charge me 3% interest. I will use the $100 to p=
ay off my depositors. I=E2=80=99ll be left with a $100 asset and a $100 lia=
