olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Signatu=
re Bank failed</a>?=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both Signature=E2=80=99s insured and uninsured=
 customers will be able to access all their deposits under the same =E2=80=
=9Csystemic risk exception=E2=80=9D that will give Silicon Valley Bank cust=
omers access to their cash starting Monday, regulators said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The decision to close Signature came as a surp=
rise to its managers, who found out shortly before the public announcement,=
 according to a person familiar with the matter. The bank faced a torrent o=
f deposit outflows on Friday, but the situation had stabilized by Sunday, t=
he person said, asking not to be identified discussing a private matter.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI think that if we=E2=80=99d been all=
owed to open tomorrow, that we could=E2=80=99ve continued =E2=80=94 we have=
 a solid loan book, we=E2=80=99re the biggest lender in New York City under=
 the low-income housing tax credit,=E2=80=9D said former Congressman Barney=
 Frank, a Signature Bank board member known for the Dodd-Frank Act, which o=
verhauled US financial regulation in the wake of the global financial crisi=
s. =E2=80=9CI think the bank could=E2=80=99ve been a going concern.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Much like Silicon Valley Bank, with clients ma=
de up almost entirely of businesses, Signature had a deposit base that was =
mostly uninsured =E2=80=94 roughly 90% of deposits for Signature, and north=
 of 93% of domestic deposits at SVB. That may have attracted the attention =
of regulators looking into banks with large uninsured deposit bases.=C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhat happened at Silvergate and SVB w=
as a very traditional bank failure,=E2=80=9D said J. Austin Campbell, an ad=
junct professor of Columbia Business School. =E2=80=9CThis, unless there wa=
s a bigger run on deposits than we know about, is less so. If there=E2=80=
=99s not some pretty gory details that came out after about the balance she=
et, it=E2=80=99s hard to figure out why they were singled out.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One notable fact is that Signature is (was?) o=
ne of the two main crypto-friendly US banks, along with Silvergate, and I s=
uppose shutting them down is appealing to bank regulators who have become v=
ery skeptical of crypto. Arguably this whole banking crisis was kicked off =
by <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30821211.285418=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMDkvY3=
J5cHRvLWJhbmstaGFkLWEtYm9yaW5nLWNvbGxhcHNlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMTMyM19NT05FWVNUV=
UZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDMx=
MyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1745a5c7" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  contagion from crypto</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0crypto exchanges banked with =
Silvergate, they lost money, they pulled it out of Silvergate, that sparked=
 a run, it spread =E2=80=94=C2=A0and regulators have been vocal about wanti=
ng to prevent further contagion from crypto into the real financial system.=
 Seizing the crypto banks is a step toward doing that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I think there=E2=80=99s another way to rea=
d this. The measures that US regulators announced yesterday =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
the BTFP and the guarantees on uninsured deposits =E2=80=94=C2=A0do in some=
 obvious sense amount to a=C2=A0<em>bailout of banks</em>. Not of Silicon V=
alley Bank, though: SVB had already been seized by the FDIC, and its shareh=
olders (and perhaps bondholders) will get zeroed. SVB took dumb risks with =
depositor money and so its investors lost everything, but the depositors wi=
ll get their money back.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But every=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>bank=E2=80=
=99s=C2=A0shareholders and bondholders and executives will benefit from tho=
se measures. If you are an uninsured depositor at a medium-sized bank that =
made some dumb rates bets, there is no reason to move your money now; the F=
ed has made it clear that it will support that bank. This (probably!) <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30821211.285418/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTMvc3ZiLWFmdG=
VybWF0aC10aGVyZS1zLWxpdHRsZS1ldmlkZW5jZS1vZi1hLWZ1bGwtc2NhbGUtYmFua2luZy1jc=
mlzaXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxMzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ec5080a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  takes run risk off the table for=
 those banks</a>, making them less likely to fail, making their stocks and =
bonds more valuable than they would be if the Fed hadn=E2=80=99t acted to l=
imit contagion. (In actual fact many bank stocks=C2=A0are <a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30821211.285418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3N=
